  <!-- ✅ 图片插入到这里 -->
  <img src="https://i.miji.bid/2025/03/24/d4f6cf985a1f90238e2350f527c67d60.webp"
       alt="图片"
       style="width: 60vw; height: auto; object-fit: contain;"><br><br>
He took the book with him after all.

Now it lay quietly on the table, as if nothing had happened, and as if it was quietly changing the timeline somewhere. The undecipherable symbols flickered slightly, as if they were dreaming-or waiting in a dream for him to wake up.

He fell asleep, the moonlight reflecting on the side of his face, making it look even more tired and real. No one knew what choice he had made, and perhaps he wasn't sure himself.

But whether the world knew it or not, he took the book with him.

It was his secret, his monument, his ...... farewell.

Do you want him to wake up? Or, is that enough?
  <strong>END</strong>
</div>


