  color: white;
">
  <p>
 That's when the phone rang, and the person on the other end, a male voice, verified his identity and said, “I really shouldn't have bothered you today, it's one of your darkest days that I remember after all these years.” The voice was peculiar, clear but seemingly distant and ethereal, and brought to his mind the image of a cold wind blowing across the strings of a harp abandoned in the wilderness. The other went on, “This day was supposed to be Wen's wedding, I do remember it after all these years, and it was this day that she invited you, but you didn't go.”

     “Which one of you?”

     “I have thought about this countless times over the years, in fact, I should have gone, so that you will be much more comfortable in your heart now, but you ...... of course you still went, hiding in the distance to watch Wen in a wedding dress pulling his hand into the hotel, this is indeed the best way for you to torture yourself.”

     “Who are you?” He asked in surprise, while noticing something strange in the other man's words: he repeated “after all these years” three times, and the wedding was actually this morning. His first thought was that these words might be a reference to the past, but he dismissed the idea immediately, for he knew that Wen's wedding date had been hastily set a week ago, and that no one in the world had known it was today before.

      The distant one went on, “You have a habit of picking at the bottom of your shoes with your left thumb dead center when you're in pain, and when you came home a while ago you noticed that your toenails were broken, but your toenails are really long now, and your socks are worn holes, and they haven't been cut in a long time, and you've been distracted for quite some time now.”

     “Who the hell are you?!” He was genuinely alarmed.

     “I'm you, calling you from ninety-eight years later, and I'm in the year 2123. It's really hard to access your mobile network from this point, the temporal interface is very lossy, so if the quality of the call is bad, just say so and we'll re-access it.”

 He knew it wasn't a joke, he knew from the start that it really wasn't a voice from this world. He gripped his cell phone tightly and froze, facing the moonlit buildings, it seemed like the whole city was frozen in time, listening to them, but he couldn't say anything for a moment, the other party waited patiently, and that's when he heard a faint background voice, “How did I ...... survive until then? ” He said casually, simply to break the silence.

     “In another twenty years or so from where you are now, gene therapy will be available and people's lifespans will be extended to around two hundred years old, I'm still considered to be in my middle age, but I feel old already.”

     “Can you go into detail about the whole thing?”

     “No, not even a brief introduction, I have to make sure you get as little information about the future as possible to avoid any inappropriate behavior from you that might change the course of history.”

     “Then why are you contacting me at all?”

     “For a mission, a mission we will share. Having lived to this age, I can tell you a trick of life: once you understand how insignificant the individual is in the vastness of time and space, you can relax about anything. I didn't contact you this time to talk about personal matters, so let go of everything personal for a moment and face this mission. Now, what do you hear?”

  [[Next|T7-2-6]]
  </p>
</div>


:: T7-2-6 {"position":"675,2150","size":"100,100"}
<div style="
